@node "fvdisnap_general" "fVDISnap: generalities"

 fVDI Catcher/Snapshot runs only as accessory.

 It generates screen (or screen parts) snapshots in GEM environment
 and uses Parx M&E WIM modules (in INLINEs) to save as:
 ú IMG (Atari format, for 1 bitplane)
 ú GIF (gif87a, for 2 to 8 bitplanes)
 ú TGA (uncompressed, for 15-32 bitplanes)

 Works
 - apparently in all ST and Falcon screen modes.
 - in 16 bits True color Eclipse/RageIIc mode
 - on FireBee in TC16, TC32, 256c and monochrome.
 - on Apollo V4SA and extended SAGA video modes.
  
@endnode

